data.enText: (in the past) the skin and hair that was removed from the head of a dead enemy by some Native American peoples as a sign of victory

data.chText: （表示某人已被打败或已受到惩罚的）标志
data.enText: a symbol of the fact that sb has been defeated or punished

data.chText: 他们已在夺取冠军的征途上获得显著进展。
data.enText: They have claimed some impressive scalps in their bid for the championship.

data.enText: to remove the skin and hair from the top of an enemy's head as a sign of victory

tr: the skin that covers the top of the head
example: they wanted to take his scalp as a trophy

tr: sell illegally, as on the black market

value.def: Your scalp is the skin under the hair on your head.

example.ex: He smoothed his hair back over his scalp...
Massage the shampoo into the scalp.
example.tran: 通过按摩让洗发香波渗入头皮。

value.def: To scalp someone means to remove the skin and hair from the top of their head.

example.ex: He pretended to scalp me with his sword.
example.tran: 他假装要用剑剥下我的头皮。

value.def: A scalp is the piece of skin and hair that is removed when someone is scalped.
If you say that you want someone's scalp, you mean that you want to defeat or punish them.

example.tran: 股票投机商想整他一顿。

example.ex: He told friends I was after his scalp.
example.tran: 他告诉朋友们我想打败他。

value.def: If someone scalps tickets, they sell them outside a sports ground or theatre, usually for more than their original value.

example.ex: He was trying to pick up some cash scalping tickets.
example.tran: 他那时正想通过倒票赚点儿钱。
